You can set up a report to run itself daily, weekly, or monthly and send the results automatically. The required editions are Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To create, edit, and delete reports, you need Enhanced Folder Sharing. To schedule reports, you also need this permission.

Schedule a Report for Refresh:
Schedule a report to run daily, weekly, or monthly.
View a Report's Schedule:
View a report's schedule on the Schedule Report page or from the Reports tab.
Manage a Report’s Schedule:
Create, change, view, or delete a scheduled report.
Change a Report's Schedule:
You can change an already scheduled report.
Delete a Report's Schedule:
Select a scheduled report and unschedule it to delete its scheduled run.

Some tips to keep in mind about timings, limits, and email notifications when scheduling a report.
title: Scheduling Reports in Salesforce
